  <a href="#1" id="1">
   LONDON -- Following his takeover of the unprofitable New York Daily News, British publisher Robert Maxwell plans to raise around #250 million ($448 million) through the sale of shares in his Mirror Group Newspapers Ltd. of Britain.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   In a flotation organized by Samuel Montagu &amp; Co., Mirror is to sell 45% to 49% of its shares to investors in Britain and abroad.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The offering is expected to value Mirror Group at more than #500 million. Mirror's flagship publication is the tabloid Daily Mirror, with sales of three million copies daily .
  </a>
